2. Is it a power issue?

No. See above. Number of fixations is significant even with 1 observation per trial. Time spent on trial and accuracy are not significant with 1 observation per trial.

3. What changed from 1000 iterations hierarchical (significant result on accuracy in original analysis) to 5000 iterations?

Distribution of beta was wider and had a negative skew.

Less skewed with 5000 iterations or with Antonia’s method

Plotting the relationships
